---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { COMPANY_NAME, BRIEF_PATH } from "../config";
---

<Layout title={`How we work — ${COMPANY_NAME}`} path="/about">
  <SiteNav variant="full" />

  <main
    class="px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16 pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32"
    style="background: var(--color-bg);"
  >
    <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h1
        class="font-serif leading-[1.02] tracking-tight"
        style="
          color: var(--color-ink);
          font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.75rem);
        "
      >
        A note on how we work.
      </h1>

      <div
        class="mt-12 md:mt-14 space-y-7 leading-relaxed"
        style="color: var(--color-ink-muted); font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1.4vw, 1.25rem); line-height: 1.7;"
      >
        <p>
          Sponsorship marketing has a sourcing problem. Databases give brands a
          list and tell them to do the rest. Agencies sell retainers built for
          someone else's scale. Most small and mid-sized brands end up running
          creator campaigns the same way they run cold email — at volume, with
          a roster they don't really know.
        </p>

        <p>
          We started CastWorks because the work between the database and the
          campaign is the work that decides whether a campaign returns. Skip
          it and the rest of the spend is a coin flip.
        </p>

        <p>
          We built our own tooling for the parts that scale. Audience analysis.
          Content fit. Commercial pattern matching. The parts that don't scale,
          we still do by hand. Reading a creator's last six months of work.
          Drafting a first message that reads like it's from a person.
          Confirming interest before any name reaches a brand.
        </p>

        <p>
          What you get is not a list. It's a curated pipeline of creators who
          already know your brief and are open to the conversation. We do this
          for a small number of brands at a time. The fewer briefs we run, the
          better each one runs.
        </p>

        <p>
          If that's the kind of partner you're looking for, submit a brief. If
          we're a fit, you'll hear back within two business days.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20">
        <a
          href={BRIEF_PATH}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-base transition-colors duration-200"
          style="color: var(--color-ink); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 6px; text-decoration-thickness: 1px;"
          onmouseover="this.style.color='var(--color-accent)'"
          onmouseout="this.style.color='var(--color-ink)'"
        >
          Submit a brief
          <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p
        class="mt-16 text-sm italic"
        style="color: var(--color-ink-subtle); font-family: var(--font-serif);"
      >
        — Ege Ipek
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
